tourBios.carHigh: 2014: Made the cut and finished T59 at the Farmers Insurance Open on the PGA TOUR in January. Prior to the start of the Mackenzie Tour season, played in four TOUR events as a sponsor exemption...Earned exempt status for the Mackenzie Tour, finishing T6 at the Canada Qualifying School...In Mackenzie Tour debut at the season-opening PC Financial Open, posted rounds of 68-66 on the weekend to finish T4, three strokes back of champion Joel Dahmen. Mackenzie Tour rookie earned second top 10 in four events at the SIGA Dakota Dunes Open. Closed with rounds of 64-68 to finish T7...In ninth start, opened with rounds of 67-67 and went on to finish T6 at the Cape Breton Celtic Classic for third top-10 finish.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Won the 2013 Ben Hogan Award for outstanding male amateur and collegiate golfer...In 2012, earned the Mark H. McCormack Award for top player in the World Amateur Golf Rankings. Won six times at University of Washington, the best all-time at the school.
